Create Backup User in MySQL (if not done yet)

CREATE USER 'backupuser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'your_password';
GRANT SELECT, LOCK TABLES, SHOW VIEW, EVENT, TRIGGER ON ss_utiity.* TO 'backupuser'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;


# Backup Script for ss_utiity
Save this as /usr/local/bin/mysql_backup_ss_utiity.sh:

#!/bin/bash

# Backup directory
BACKUP_DIR="/var/backups/mysql"
DATE=$(date +"%Y-%m-%d_%H-%M-%S")

# MySQL credentials
MYSQL_USER="backupuser"
MYSQL_PASS="your_password"

# Database name
DATABASE_NAME="ss_utiity"

# Create backup directory if needed
mkdir -p "$BACKUP_DIR"

# Backup command with compression and single transaction
mysqldump -u"$MYSQL_USER" -p"$MYSQL_PASS" --single-transaction "$DATABASE_NAME" | gzip > "$BACKUP_DIR/${DATABASE_NAME}_$DATE.sql.gz"

# Optional: remove backups older than 7 days
find "$BACKUP_DIR" -type f -name "${DATABASE_NAME}_*.sql.gz" -mtime +7 -exec rm {} \;

# Log success message
echo "Backup for $DATABASE_NAME completed at $DATE"


Make it executable:
chmod +x /usr/local/bin/mysql_backup_ss_utiity.sh

Schedule Backup Using Cron
Edit your crontab:

crontab -e

Add this line to run the backup every day at 2:30 AM:
mi hr
30 2 * * * /usr/local/bin/mysql_backup_ss_utiity.sh >> /var/log/mysql_backup_ss_utiity.log 2>&1

* * * * * command_to_run
| | | | |
| | | | +----- Day of the Week (0-7) (Sunday=0 or 7)
| | | +------- Month (1-12)
| | +--------- Day of the Month (1-31)
| +----------- Hour (0-23)
+------------- Minute (0-59)


| Position | Field        | Allowed Values                    | Meaning of `*`     |
| -------- | ------------ | --------------------------------- | ------------------ |
| 1        | Minute       | 0-59                              | Every minute       |
| 2        | Hour         | 0-23                              | Every hour         |
| 3        | Day of Month | 1-31                              | Every day of month |
| 4        | Month        | 1-12 or Jan-Dec                   | Every month        |
| 5        | Day of Week  | 0-7 or Sun-Sat (0 and 7 = Sunday) | Every day of week  |



Thatâ€™s it!
Backups will be saved compressed in /var/backups/mysql

Older backups (7+ days) will be auto-deleted

Logs will be in /var/log/mysql_backup_ss_utiity.log




